  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.1 (all)\r\nOS & Version: all\r\nCommit hash: -\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nWhile using `syncmode light` it was expected the `get_transactionReceipt` method would return the same data as `syncmode fast/full`. However, `contractAddress` returns `null`, causing disruption of Dapps. \r\n\r\nUIs shouldn't have to worry about dealing with mode-specific behavior. Ideally, they would just rely on the same API.\r\n\r\nIn Mist we've circumvented that by intercepting the RPC method and [applying the necessary measures](https://github.com/ethereum/mist/blob/develop/modules/ipc/methods/eth_getTransactionReceipt.js#L39-L57). \r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`contractAddress` always returns `null` while running with `syncmode light`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nRun `eth_getTransactionReceipt` with a tx hash of a created contract.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nnone\r\n````",
